Here's a simple JavaScript program that generates and prints out the ASCII character and hexadecimal codes for values from 0 to 127 (0x7F):
```javascript
for(let i = 0; i <= 0x7f; i++) {
    let charCode = String.fromCharCode(i);
    console.log(`${charCode}: ASCII ${i}, Hexadecimal ${i.toString(16)}`);
}
```

This program uses a `for` loop to iterate over the range of values from 0 to 127 (inclusive). For each value, it generates the corresponding ASCII character using the `String.fromCharCode()` method and stores it in the `charCode` variable.

The program then prints out the generated ASCII character, its decimal ASCII code (`i`), and its hexadecimal representation (`i.toString(16)`) to the console using a template literal string.

Note that this program only generates codes for values up to 0x7F (127), as requested in the question. If you need codes for higher values, simply adjust the loop condition accordingly.
